    {
      "id": "ddr-fm-help-SiZhbXA7-99",
      "position": {
        "x": 89,
        "y": 632,
        "width": 429,
        "height": 110,
        "z": 11
      },
      "props": {
        "styleTheme": "Classic",
        "ddrObjectPath": "99",
        "rotation": 0,
        "autosizeTop": true,
        "autosizeRight": false,
        "autosizeBottom": false,
        "autosizeLeft": true,
        "ddrOriginalObjectType": "Text",
        "ddrObjectFlags": 0,
        "ddrAnchorSource": "flags",
        "ddrStyleParsed": true,
        "ddrConditionalFormattingStatic": false,
        "ddrSourceTop": 632,
        "ddrSourceLeft": 89,
        "ddrSourceBottom": 742,
        "ddrSourceRight": 518,
        "fillType": "none",
        "lineColor": "rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)",
        "lineStyle": "solid",
        "effectOuterShadow": false,
        "fontFamily": "Verdana",
        "fontSize": 10,
        "textColor": "#000000",
        "label": "Layouts are where information (records) is entered that is specific to that layout.  Layouts can be accessed in two ways (1) by clicking on a button or (2) by accessing the Layout Menu in the status area; this is located near the top of the status area, where you click to access the menu is on the oblong with a blue arrow attached. \n\nWhen you click on your choice of layout the system will automatically bring that layout to the screen.  An example of a layout would be; the “Job Review - Today” layout is where you enter information for new Jobs or the “Contacts” layout is where you enter information for a client or supplier.",
        "ddrArrangeOrder": 11
      },
      "type": "label"
    },
    {
      "id": "ddr-fm-help-SiZhbXA7-100",
      "position": {
        "x": 95,
        "y": 827,
        "width": 419,
        "height": 86,
        "z": 12
      },
      "props": {
        "styleTheme": "Classic",
        "ddrObjectPath": "100",
        "rotation": 0,
        "autosizeTop": true,
        "autosizeRight": false,
        "autosizeBottom": false,
        "autosizeLeft": true,
        "ddrOriginalObjectType": "Text",
        "ddrObjectFlags": 0,
        "ddrAnchorSource": "flags",
        "ddrStyleParsed": true,
        "ddrConditionalFormattingStatic": false,
        "ddrSourceTop": 827,
        "ddrSourceLeft": 95,
        "ddrSourceBottom": 913,
        "ddrSourceRight": 514,
        "fillType": "none",
        "lineColor": "rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)",
        "lineStyle": "solid",
        "effectOuterShadow": false,
        "fontFamily": "Verdana",
        "fontSize": 10,
        "textColor": "#000000",
        "label": "Tables are what make up a database.  In the Jaeger & Ernst database we have multiple tables, some are linked to each other by a common piece of information. An example would be a particular client in the “Clients Table” may have many records in the “Job Review Table” for all the projects we have done for that client.\n\nAs you enter information in a layout you are adding records to that table.",
        "ddrArrangeOrder": 12
      },
      "type": "label"
    },
    {
      "id": "ddr-fm-help-SiZhbXA7-101",
      "position": {
        "x": 94,
        "y": 785,
        "width": 419,
        "height": 33,
        "z": 13
      },
      "props": {
        "styleTheme": "Classic",
        "ddrObjectPath": "101",
        "rotation": 0,
        "autosizeTop": true,
        "autosizeRight": false,
        "autosizeBottom": false,
        "autosizeLeft": true,
        "ddrOriginalObjectType": "Text",
        "ddrObjectFlags": 0,
        "ddrAnchorSource": "flags",
        "ddrStyleParsed": true,
        "ddrConditionalFormattingStatic": false,
        "ddrSourceTop": 785,
        "ddrSourceLeft": 94,
        "ddrSourceBottom": 818,
        "ddrSourceRight": 513,
        "fillType": "none",
        "lineColor": "rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)",
        "lineStyle": "solid",
        "effectOuterShadow": false,
        "fontFamily": "Verdana",
        "fontSize": 10,
        "textColor": "#000000",
        "label": "A database is a group of tables, some are related to one another through a common thread of information.",
        "ddrArrangeOrder": 13
      },
      "type": "label"
    },
    {
      "id": "ddr-fm-help-SiZhbXA7-104",
      "position": {
        "x": 78,
        "y": 108,
        "width": 425,
        "height": 398,
        "z": 14
      },
      "props": {
        "styleTheme": "Classic",
        "ddrObjectPath": "104",
        "rotation": 0,
        "autosizeTop": true,
        "autosizeRight": false,
        "autosizeBottom": false,
        "autosizeLeft": true,
        "ddrOriginalObjectType": "Text",
        "ddrObjectFlags": 0,
        "ddrAnchorSource": "flags",
        "ddrStyleParsed": true,
        "ddrConditionalFormattingStatic": false,
        "ddrSourceTop": 108,
        "ddrSourceLeft": 78,
        "ddrSourceBottom": 506,
        "ddrSourceRight": 503,
        "fillType": "none",
        "lineColor": "rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)",
        "lineStyle": "solid",
        "effectOuterShadow": false,
        "fontFamily": "Verdana",
        "fontSize": 10,
        "textColor": "#000000",
        "label": "The “Status Area” is on the left side of your screen. At the very top it tells you what “Mode” you are in.(Browse, layout, find or preview).  \n\nUnder the heading that tells you what mode you are in is the heading “Layout:” and under this heading is an oblong with a blue arrow on the right end. Within this oblong is the name of the layout that is currently displayed on your screen. \n\nIf you click on the arrow another window of information will open.  This window will will display a list of layouts, and if you click on the name of the layout it will display on your screen. Please do not do this in this window. \n\nNext you will see something that looks like an open book, with a round blue slider under it.  This book allows you to page from one record to another by clicking on the left or right page.  If you want to progress faster through the records you can use the round blue slider.  If you hold your cursor over the slider and drag it to the left or the right it will progress you through the records in the direction you slide.\n\nAs you go down the “Status Area” you will next see a window with a number displayed.  This tells you the number of the record that is being displayed on your screen based on the “Total” number of records.  The “Total:”number of records viewable is indicated below this window.  \n\nNext you will see the word “unsorted” - this tells you the order of the total records viewable.\n\nWhen you are in a layout that creates records for a table you will see the following;  Next is the word “Script:”. Below this are two oblongs - one with the word “Continue” highlighted in blue and one with the word “Cancel” within the oblong.  \n\nAfter you are finished viewing this help window click on the oblong that is highlighted in blue and says “Continue”",
        "ddrArrangeOrder": 14
      },
      "type": "label"
    },
